div.p: Histopathological evaluation of the liver of the control and stressed groups, samples were stained with hematoxillin and eosin, the arrows represent pathological changes in tissue: ( a) control groups: normal tissue ×200; ( b) H 2O 2 group: dilatation in the central vein ×200; ( c) H 2O 2 group: binucleation ×400; ( d) H 2O 2 group: inflammation ×400; ( e) H 2O 2 + Argan: dilatation in the central vein ×100; ( f) H 2O 2 + Argan + Syzygium aromaticum essential oil group: dilatation in the central vein ×200.
